-- Why these will stop the “Bronze > Raw” reconciliation failures

-- Your earlier ISO-week reconciliations were comparing:

-- RAW filtered by file_load_datetime (merge scope), but

-- BRONZE filtered only by date/week (not by file_load_datetime)

-- So Bronze naturally included older loads (and sometimes extra historical grain combos), causing Bronze totals to exceed RAW.

-- In these procedures, reconciliation compares raw_dedup vs bronze_scope where both are filtered to the same merge lookback on file_load_datetime and the same recent date window — so, if your merge is correct, expected and actual should line up.